{"word":"σκοπέω","slug":"σκοπέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>σκοπέω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:σκοπός'><el>σκοπός</el></a>\n<br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>used by <a href='S:Attic, in Attic Greek'>Att.</a> writers only in <a href='S:present tense'>pres.</a> and <a href='S:imperfect tense'>impf.</a>, the other tenses being supplied by <el>σκέπτομαι.</el>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to look at</i> or <i>after</i> a thing: <i>to behold, contemplate</i>, <b><a href='S:Pindar'>Pind.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>:—<a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a> <i>to look out, watch</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>to look to, consider, examine</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, attic; <el>σκ. τι</el> <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; <el>σκ. περί τινος</el> or <el>τι</el> <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>: <a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a>, <el>ὀρθῶς σκοπεῖν</el> <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><i>to look out for</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a>, used just like <a href='S:active signification'><a href='S:Active voice'>Act.</a></a>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>III. </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, <el>σκοπῶν καὶ σκοπούμενος</el> <i>considering</i> and <i>being considered</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}